org.vadere.util.data

Class Table

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.vadere.util.data.Table
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Row>

    public class Table
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Row>
    The Table is an abstract data type with a fixed column size (fixed numbers of columns and fixed column names). Null entries are not allowed. If you try to get an value from an entry outside the range this may result in an IllegalArgumentException. Column names are unique. It is possible to merge a table in an existing table, if they both has the same number of rows. One can only insert values at the end of the table. You have to complete a whole row before you can insert another one. The only possibility to delete manipulate existing rows is to use the iterators RowIterator or RowArrayIterator. The reason is that it is inefficient to reference via index since the implementation is based on LinkedList. Note: The column size difference is maximal +-1, if the row is not complete. This implementation is not synchronized.

      • addColumnEntry

        public void addColumnEntry(java.lang.String columnName,
                           java.lang.Object value)
        Adds a value to the specific column of the current row identified by a column name. Note that one has to fill a whole row before add a new row. After a row is complete one has to call addRow(). If the column does not exist an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown. If one try to add an entry to a full column an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        columnName - name of the column
        value - the value that will be inserted
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the column does not exist
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the column is full before the call is happened

        public void addRow()

      • merge

        public void merge(Table table)
        Merges a table into this table by add each column to this table. Both tables has to be of the same size. If there a duplicated column names this table will stay with its column. Futhermore the columns of the other table will be added behind the this table.
        Parameters:
        table - the table that will be merged into this table
